data.content:
## What breaks: Sync I/O on EF Core Cosmos is **fully removed** in .NET 11

In .NET 10, calling `ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, `SaveChanges()`, etc. on the Cosmos provider was unsupported by default but could be re-enabled with an opt-in. **In EF Core 11, that opt-in is gone.** All synchronous I/O calls **always throw** — no workaround.

### Every method in your repository breaks:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();     // was ToList()
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id); // was First()
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();      // was Count()
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();                // was SaveChanges()
    }
}
```

### Quick reference for the conversion:

| .NET 10 (sync) | .NET 11 (required async) |
|-----------------|--------------------------|
| `ToList()` | `await ToListAsync()` |
| `First()` | `await FirstAsync()` |
| `Count()` | `await CountAsync()` |
| `SaveChanges()` | `await SaveChangesAsync()` |

This will ripple through your callers — every method consuming the repository will also need to become `async Task<T>`. Tracking issue: [dotnet/efcore#37059](https://github.com/dotnet/efcore/issues/37059).
